The paper discusses the application of antifragility to intelligent autonomous systems, specifically those based on AI-planning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents a case study of an autonomous wheeled robot, indicating relevance to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The proposed architecture is designed to impart antifragility to the system, which involves self-improvement and adaptation, suggesting relevance to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of AI-planning, which is a sub-field of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes an architecture that allows the system to uncover new capabilities, indicating relevance to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
